summary: The document is a secret receipt for authentication materials related to the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992. It acknowledges the receipt of various Cuban documents including a passport, visa, and vaccination certificate, issued to Javier Alvarez de la Torre. The materials were to be returned to the CIA after their operational use was fulfilled.
key_findings: The document is part of the records released under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
It details the receipt of authentication materials for operational use, including a Cuban passport and visa.
The materials were issued to an individual named Javier Alvarez de la Torre.
Instructions specify the return of unused or no longer needed documents to the CIA's Technical Services Division (TSD/IB).
keywords: President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act
